title: Pennsylvania’s Senate candidates make their final pitches: We’re not politicians.
dc:creator: Blake Hounshell

media:content.media:credit: Hilary Swift for The New York Times, Ruth Fremson/The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Dr. Mehmet Oz, Pennsylvania’s Republican nominee for Senate, and Lt. Gov John Fetterman, the Democratic candidate, have both settled on the same theme in the final days leading up to the election: Politicians can’t be trusted.
